<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lip1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lip,</orth> subst. the border of the mouth: <bibl n="shak. ven 19" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 19" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 19</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.238" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 238</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 1, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.220" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 220</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.140" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 140</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.192.140" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 192</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.192.140" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 192</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.192.140" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 192</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.4.16" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.120" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.180" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 180</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.4.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 4, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.265" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 5, 265</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.76" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.1.158" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.161.158" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 161</bibl> etc. <emph>to bite the l.,</emph> a sign of anger: <bibl n="shak. shr 2.250" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 250</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.1.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 1, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 43</bibl>. or of a mind absorbed in thought: <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.254" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 254</bibl>. <cit><quote>falling a l. of much contempt,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.373" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 373</bibl></cit>; cf. <cit><quote>marked you his l. and eyes?</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.259" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 259</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he hangs the l. at something,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.1.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 1, 152</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I will make a l. at the physician,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 127</bibl></cit> (laugh at him, snap my fingers at him). <cit><quote>steeped me in poverty to the very --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 50</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>kiss the --s of unacquainted change,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.166" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 166</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the murmuring --s of discontent,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.53" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 53</bibl></cit>. As organs of speech, <emph>--s</emph> almost == mouth: <cit><quote>she stops his --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 46" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 46</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>mercy will breathe within your --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 78</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I will open my --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.199" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 199</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.84" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 2</bibl>. <cit><quote>locked within the teeth and the --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 143</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--s, do not move,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 109</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 179</bibl>. <cit><quote>hold close thy --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.118" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 118</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his slanderous --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 24</bibl></cit>. <emph>lay thy finger on thy --s</emph> (be silent) <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.240" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 240</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 187</bibl> etc.

